                <p>Le Creuset is responsible for some of the most premium cookware on the planet. The company has been around since 1925, churning out luxurious products that donâ€™t just look fantastic, but also hold up to extreme use in the kitchen--making them durable, long-lasting products with a massive community of dedicated fans. The company has now teamed up with Pokemon to launch a limited-edition <a href="https://clicks.trx-hub.com/xid/fandom_32094_gamespot?q=https%3A%2F%2Fgo.skimresources.com%3Fid%3D225336X1707200%26xs%3D1%26xcust%3Dsubid_value%26url%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.bokksu.com%2Fcollections%2Fpokemon-le-creuset-collection&amp;p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Farticles%2Fthis-very-fancy-pokemon-cookware-line-includes-129-mug-999-pot%2F1100-6530105%2F&amp;event_type=click" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Pokemon x Le Creuset Collection</a>. And while none of the products are cheap, they're incredibly premium and ultra-adorable.</p><p>As expected, these items are selling out fast. The four most affordable items have already sold out, but you can sign up to be notified when they're back in stock. This includes three different Kutaniyaki Sobachoco Cups and the Kutaniyaki Mini Plate, which cost $99 and $85, respectively. Crafted by the renowned Kutaniyaki kiln, Seikogama, they're a premium way to enjoy soups, drinks, and snacks.</p><figure data-align="center" data-size="large" data-img-src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1702/17023653/4458879-mixcollage-13-mar-2025-08-46-am-5228.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-4458879" data-ratio="0.563" data-width="1000" data-embed-type="image"><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1702/17023653/4458879-mixcollage-13-mar-2025-08-46-am-5228.jpg" data-ref-id="1300-4458879"></a><figcaption>Pokemon x Le Creuset Cocotte Ronde and Mugs</figcaption><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1702/17023653/4458879-mixcollage-13-mar-2025-08-46-am-5228.jpg"></figure><figure dat